259
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:59,041
Some people went down there
to check it out,

260
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:01,043
but none of them made it back.

261
00:16:04,588 --> 00:16:06,757
Ma'am, wait up.

262
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:36,161
-Don't you see that?
-Pardon me?

263
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:38,163
My Chanel is there.

264
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:41,250
-You mean, this?
-That's not what I meant.

265
00:16:41,417 --> 00:16:43,043
That's Chanel's seat.

266
00:16:43,502 --> 00:16:45,045
Don't you get it?

267
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,843
You can sit here. I'm done.

268
00:16:58,183 --> 00:17:00,019
Enjoy your lunch.

269
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,688
-I don't need this.
-My gosh.

270
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:09,111
Obnoxious people are everywhere.

271
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:11,905
Are you not going to eat this?

272
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,242
No.

273
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:24,001
Actually, I hate everyone here.

274
00:17:26,503 --> 00:17:27,838
STATIONERY

275
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,633
Please! Please.

276
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,222
Darn it!

277
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:40,934
What are you doing here?

278
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,936
I'm doing this to go to the buffet
with you.

279
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:44,146
Come out!

280
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:46,190
Come out.

281
00:17:53,697 --> 00:17:54,907
I didn't get it again.

282
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:57,701
Wait, are you trying get that one?
That steel ring?

283
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:01,538
Are you planning to seduce me
with that ring?

284
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:02,831
That 500-won ring?

285
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,958
When it comes to gifts,
what it is doesn't matter.

286
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:06,960
What's important is who gave it to you.

287
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,170
You drive me bonkers.

288
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:12,716
-You used to like me.
-Gosh!

289
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:16,970
Stop talking about the old days.
It offends me.

290
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:29,316
They must be selling an expensive
item by treating the elders well.

291
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:33,779
I wonder if
his investigation is going well.

292
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:41,829
Oh, ma'am.

293
00:18:43,789 --> 00:18:44,873
It's okay. Relax.

294
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:47,584
You don't have to put on an act
when it's just the two of us.

295
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:49,128
I'm on your side, you know.

296
00:18:50,504 --> 00:18:53,090
There will be fun performances
later. You should stay for them.

297
00:18:53,674 --> 00:18:57,010
You really look like an employee here.

298
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,263
I am an employee here.

299
00:18:59,471 --> 00:19:01,181
I know everything.

300
00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,809
You're here as an undercover reporter.

301
00:19:03,892 --> 00:19:07,855
My gosh. Ma'am, it looks like
you got the wrong idea.

302
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,023
I'm not here as an undercover reporter,

303
00:19:10,107 --> 00:19:12,067
and I'm not even a reporter to begin with.

304
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,610
Are they bugging this room?

305
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,195
Gosh, what are you talking about?

306
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:20,742
-There are no bugging devices here.
-My gosh.

307
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:23,871
What's the matter with this lady?

308
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:25,873
She's very funny.

309
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:28,041
She thought I was here
as an undercover reporter.

310
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:30,043
Ma'am, I'm not a reporter.

311
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:33,213
-I guess you mistook me for--
-No, I didn't.

312
00:19:33,297 --> 00:19:35,048
You know me well.

313
00:19:35,299 --> 00:19:36,925
I know this guy well.

314
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,678
I see. I, too, know this guy very well.

315
00:19:40,053 --> 00:19:41,555
I've known him for 20 years.

316
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:43,849
-Right? Hasn't it been 20 years?
-Yes, it's been 20 years.

317
00:19:49,563 --> 00:19:53,025
Do you really work here? Why?

318
00:19:53,901 --> 00:19:55,027
This place is nice.

319
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:56,778
Try all the classes today.

320
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:59,281
If you still don't want to stay,
I won't stop you.

321
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:02,034
Promise?

322
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,373
It's a promise.

323
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:14,213
Hey. You really...

324
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,090
What is going on?

325
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:20,469
Jun-ha really works here?

326
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:22,763
Why?

327
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:25,307
Why is working here better
than being a reporter?

328
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:26,683
Money?

329
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,894
Even if he wants a lot of money...

330
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:35,442
Seriously. Even after seeing this?

331
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:39,780
Why do they even take a nap as a group?

332
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:43,659
How can they sleep at a place like this?

333
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:46,245
They're not even home.

334
00:20:56,004 --> 00:20:57,256
Welcome.

335
00:21:00,926 --> 00:21:02,970
What are you doing here?
Where is Sang-eun?

336
00:21:03,053 --> 00:21:04,471
Hyeon-ju, you're here.

337
00:21:04,554 --> 00:21:05,889
I'm over here!

338
00:21:05,973 --> 00:21:08,517
Yeong-su is helping me out.

339
00:21:09,226 --> 00:21:10,310
That's unexpected.

340
00:21:15,774 --> 00:21:19,486
CRAB TUNA MAYONNAISE

341
00:21:22,322 --> 00:21:23,282
What's that?

342
00:21:23,365 --> 00:21:25,075
You must be hungry.

343
00:21:25,242 --> 00:21:27,953
You're too busy during lunch time
at the restaurant.

344
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:30,539
This is the only time you can eat,
but you came here.

345
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,624
You must be sick of leftover Chinese food.

346
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,220
Give it to me.

347
00:21:46,638 --> 00:21:48,890
All you can do is make noodles

348
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,392
and ride a motorcycle.

349
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:52,811
You can't do anything on your own.

350
00:21:56,648 --> 00:21:57,899
Here.

351
00:22:03,947 --> 00:22:05,115
Hey.

352
00:22:06,950 --> 00:22:08,702
Are you hitting on me?

353
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:10,078
No.

354
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:14,291
I do what I want to do as your man.

355
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:15,876
If you feel touched...

356
00:22:17,586 --> 00:22:19,504
or fall for me,

357
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:21,465
that's your responsibility.

358
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:29,973
Ridiculous.

359
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:35,062
When the director comes,
introduce yourself right away.

360
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:36,813
-This is your chance.
-Okay.

361
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,023
Thank you for giving me chance.

362
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:39,107
-No problem.
-I'll work hard.

363
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,025
-Do your best.
-Okay.

364
00:22:40,108 --> 00:22:41,818
-Here he comes.
-Hello.

365
00:22:41,902 --> 00:22:43,111
Hello.

366
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:47,657
This is Byung-man, a friend of mine.

367
00:22:47,824 --> 00:22:48,992
I'll work hard.

368
00:22:49,117 --> 00:22:50,410
What is he doing here?

369
00:22:50,577 --> 00:22:53,121
I'm thinking of putting him
on the stage later.

370
00:22:53,455 --> 00:22:54,956
-What can he do?
-Well...

371
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:56,166
He can do a strength show.

372
00:22:56,333 --> 00:22:57,751
-You're good at it, right?
-Yes.

373
00:22:58,126 --> 00:22:59,127
Show him.

374
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:04,591
That's enough.

375
00:23:04,674 --> 00:23:05,675
Can you try something else?

376
00:23:05,759 --> 00:23:07,511
-You can spin nunchaku.
-Yes.

377
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:08,720
I can spin two.

378
00:23:09,721 --> 00:23:10,806
Hey.

379
00:23:11,181 --> 00:23:13,391
This is better than the newspaper.

380
00:23:13,642 --> 00:23:14,684
Try it later.

381
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:15,852
Okay.

382
00:23:16,061 --> 00:23:17,938
I'll try to be calm. Thank you so much.

383
00:23:18,021 --> 00:23:19,815
Yes, try to be calm.

384
00:23:24,277 --> 00:23:27,155
Ma'am, do you see
that empty seat over there?

385
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:28,115
You can sit there.

386
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:30,075
I'm leaving soon.

387
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:31,785
Suit yourself then.

388
00:23:58,311 --> 00:23:59,312
-Oh, my.
-No!

389
00:23:59,396 --> 00:24:00,689
-Be careful.
-It must be hot.

390
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:11,074
What is he doing?

391
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:12,826
-Oh, my.
-Oh, no.

392
00:24:16,288 --> 00:24:17,330
My goodness.

393
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:19,166
This man here

394
00:24:19,249 --> 00:24:22,377
couldn't even walk three months ago.

395
00:24:22,711 --> 00:24:26,006
How did he become so strong
even without much training?

396
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:29,217
It's because his bones have become strong.

397
00:24:29,342 --> 00:24:32,179
Do you want to see
how strong his bones are?

398
00:24:32,262 --> 00:24:33,555
Let me show you.

399
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,933
Do you see this?

400
00:24:37,017 --> 00:24:39,436
This is used to hold up heavy things

401
00:24:39,519 --> 00:24:41,146
at construction sites.

402
00:24:41,313 --> 00:24:43,982
I'm going to hit this man
with this stick now.

403
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:46,193
The stick might break,

404
00:24:46,443 --> 00:24:48,445
but this man won't.

405
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:58,705
Let me try again.

406
00:24:58,788 --> 00:24:59,789
Here we go.

407
00:25:01,124 --> 00:25:02,125
My goodness.

408
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:03,793
Oh, no.

409
00:25:07,672 --> 00:25:08,882
You didn't break it beforehand?

410
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:10,884
I was supposed to?

411
00:25:14,179 --> 00:25:15,513
Do you hear that sound?

412
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:17,766
He might look okay on the outside,

413
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:20,852
but his bones are wrecked inside.

414
00:25:20,936 --> 00:25:22,604
Do you know why?

415
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:23,939
His bones are too weak.

416
00:25:24,147 --> 00:25:26,483
I told him

417
00:25:26,608 --> 00:25:28,193
to take this supplement,

418
00:25:28,276 --> 00:25:30,612
but he didn't listen to me.

419
00:25:30,695 --> 00:25:32,822
That's why his bones are wrecked now.

420
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:34,908
Take the supplement from now on.

421
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:36,159
Thank you.

422
00:25:36,368 --> 00:25:37,744
You can leave the stage now.

423
00:25:37,827 --> 00:25:39,996
Let's give him a big hand.

424
00:25:44,501 --> 00:25:45,877
Take the supplement.

425
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:49,422
Take the supplement for three days,
and you'll be fine.

426
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:53,093
He ended up in that state

427
00:25:53,176 --> 00:25:55,887
because his bones are weak.

428
00:25:56,096 --> 00:25:58,682
And what's crucial to bone health?

429
00:25:58,765 --> 00:25:59,891
-Calcium.
-Calcium.

430
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:01,309
You all seem to know.

431
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:04,771
That's right.
Our special technology allows us

432
00:26:05,438 --> 00:26:06,982
to concentrate calcium.

433
00:26:07,065 --> 00:26:08,233
It's right here.

434
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:09,526
Concentrated calcium.

435
00:26:09,609 --> 00:26:10,944
I knew it.

436
00:26:11,111 --> 00:26:12,654
Here it comes.

437
00:26:13,029 --> 00:26:14,489
All right. Take a look.

438
00:26:14,781 --> 00:26:17,284
This contains calcium

439
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:20,787
plus vitamins A, B, C, and D.

440
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:22,789
Low energy in the morning?

441
00:26:22,872 --> 00:26:25,250
Blurry vision? Dry mouth?

442
00:26:25,333 --> 00:26:27,002
Cracked nails?

443
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:28,878
Take three of these pills a day

444
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,755
for just a month.

445
00:26:30,839 --> 00:26:33,800
All of those symptoms will disappear.

446
00:26:33,883 --> 00:26:35,302
You're trying too hard.

447
00:26:35,385 --> 00:26:38,680
Everyone, you don't have to buy this.

448
00:26:39,347 --> 00:26:40,932
We don't want you to think

449
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:43,310
we're only being nice to you
to sell things.

450
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:46,438
You don't have to buy anything.
Just come here to have fun.

451
00:26:46,521 --> 00:26:48,898
On your way out,
take a box of tissues for free.

452
00:26:49,024 --> 00:26:52,235
Then you'll lose money.

453
00:26:52,402 --> 00:26:53,945
We just want to show our respect.

454
00:26:54,029 --> 00:26:56,031
We don't care about money.

455
00:26:56,114 --> 00:26:58,700
Don't you have to sell something
to get paid?

456
00:26:58,825 --> 00:27:01,244
-Exactly.
-You're right.

457
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:03,496
But we'd rather lose our money.

458
00:27:03,580 --> 00:27:07,083
It'd be too much trouble
for you to pay back the money.

459
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:10,295
You're giving us so much for free.
We feel bad.

460
00:27:10,378 --> 00:27:12,756
We're giving it to you
because you deserve it.

461
00:27:12,839 --> 00:27:14,007
This is a new approach.

462
00:27:14,090 --> 00:27:16,926
It's true that these calcium
and vitamin supplements

463
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:18,762
are good for you.

464
00:27:19,012 --> 00:27:20,221
I'm speaking from experience.

465
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:21,723
There you go.

466
00:27:21,973 --> 00:27:23,141
Nice build-up.

467
00:27:23,224 --> 00:27:25,310
Calcium strengthens your bones,

468
00:27:25,393 --> 00:27:27,687
and the vitamins

469
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:30,398
will fill you up with energy each morning.

470
00:27:30,482 --> 00:27:31,566
Still,

471
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:33,651
you don't have to buy it.

472
00:27:33,818 --> 00:27:36,154
This supplement sure can make you

473
00:27:36,363 --> 00:27:38,865
stronger and younger in a short time.

474
00:27:38,990 --> 00:27:40,867
However, if you come here,

475
00:27:40,950 --> 00:27:43,870
work out, and laugh together,

476
00:27:43,995 --> 00:27:46,122
it'll have a similar effect

477
00:27:46,206 --> 00:27:49,709
even though it might take longer.

478
00:27:49,876 --> 00:27:52,170
So don't feel pressured
to buy this supplement.

479
00:27:52,253 --> 00:27:55,006
He's right.
Please give Mr. Lee a big hand.

480
00:27:55,882 --> 00:27:57,801
You really don't have to buy it.

481
00:27:57,926 --> 00:27:59,010
I want one.

482
00:27:59,094 --> 00:28:01,554
Please don't buy it.

483
00:28:01,638 --> 00:28:03,181
-Just take a look.
-I want one too.

484
00:28:03,723 --> 00:28:05,058
-Just take a look.
-One here!

485
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:06,559
One over there.

486
00:28:06,643 --> 00:28:08,645
-I want two.
-You want two?

487
00:28:09,229 --> 00:28:10,271
I want two.

488
00:28:11,773 --> 00:28:13,817
They're selling supplements after all.

489
00:28:15,110 --> 00:28:17,112
Try and convince me.

490
00:28:17,195 --> 00:28:18,655
I'll never fall for it.

491
00:28:18,780 --> 00:28:19,989
See you on Monday.

492
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:26,788
I totally feel the holes in my bones
filling up.

493
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:28,581
I probably won't return it.

494
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,584
But I don't have any money.

495
00:28:31,709 --> 00:28:33,461
I'll have to ask Mom for help.

496
00:28:39,092 --> 00:28:41,052
Why are you already home?

497
00:28:41,302 --> 00:28:42,846
Mr. Jeong is going somewhere tomorrow.

498
00:28:42,929 --> 00:28:44,139
So we switched.

499
00:28:44,764 --> 00:28:46,224
He is working today instead of me.

500
00:28:47,142 --> 00:28:49,018
There is no cooked rice.

501
00:28:49,185 --> 00:28:50,562
Just start it.

502
00:28:52,939 --> 00:28:54,274
There is no hot water in the shop?

503
00:28:54,399 --> 00:28:56,401
The instant hot water dispenser
is broken again.

504
00:28:57,402 --> 00:28:59,487
You have to hold down the button
for quite a while.

505
00:29:13,960 --> 00:29:15,170
It's not washed.

506
00:29:22,135 --> 00:29:23,595
How was it today?

507
00:29:24,012 --> 00:29:25,054
Was it fun?

508
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:26,222
Not really.

509
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:28,516
There were only old people.

510
00:29:28,600 --> 00:29:29,684
It wasn't fun.

511
00:29:31,144 --> 00:29:35,190
I really don't mind.
You can stay home if you want.

512
00:29:35,273 --> 00:29:37,942
You don't have to force yourself
to go there.

513
00:29:40,195 --> 00:29:41,946
Do you have something to tell me?

514
00:29:42,071 --> 00:29:43,198
No.

515
00:29:43,531 --> 00:29:44,824
Well...

516
00:29:46,951 --> 00:29:48,661
-Mom.
-What is it?

517
00:29:49,162 --> 00:29:50,371
Just

518
00:29:51,247 --> 00:29:54,751
don't grab anything
until I'm done talking.

519
00:29:54,834 --> 00:29:55,919
Okay.

520
00:29:56,085 --> 00:29:57,670
Come on.

521
00:29:58,338 --> 00:30:02,884
Your 25-year-old daughter...

522
00:30:03,301 --> 00:30:04,344
What?

523
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:06,721
My nails keep getting cracked.

524
00:30:07,972 --> 00:30:10,099
I told you to wear gloves.

525
00:30:10,266 --> 00:30:13,186
How could you touch those chemicals
with your bare hands!

526
00:30:13,269 --> 00:30:15,772
-Let me see.
-I'm fine.

527
00:30:15,897 --> 00:30:17,565
I have to wash their hair

528
00:30:17,649 --> 00:30:21,528
and curl their hair right away.
When can I wear gloves?

529
00:30:22,278 --> 00:30:23,738
What were you saying?

