00:43:47,082 --> 00:43:48,709
Gosh, Hyeon-ju. My leg hurts so much.

789
00:43:48,917 --> 00:43:50,794
It looks like you'll have to walk me home.

790
00:43:50,878 --> 00:43:52,880
You're being ridiculous. Get lost!

791
00:43:55,716 --> 00:43:56,800
Stand tall!

792
00:43:57,176 --> 00:43:58,385
Be confident!

793
00:44:21,116 --> 00:44:22,534
I found this on the street.

794
00:44:24,703 --> 00:44:25,829
Yeong-su.

795
00:44:26,413 --> 00:44:27,873
This is so pretty.

796
00:44:28,123 --> 00:44:29,833
It's not the ring that's pretty.

797
00:44:31,043 --> 00:44:32,127
Your hand is pretty.

798
00:44:36,757 --> 00:44:37,883
I was crazy.

799
00:44:38,550 --> 00:44:39,802
I must've been out of my mind.

800
00:44:47,601 --> 00:44:48,644
Darn it!

801
00:44:50,729 --> 00:44:51,772
One, two.

802
00:44:54,608 --> 00:44:57,569
They really should use
one-touch lids for these things.

803
00:45:01,365 --> 00:45:03,534
I'll sprain my wrist at this rate.

804
00:45:06,203 --> 00:45:08,205
I need to protect my voice.

805
00:45:18,882 --> 00:45:21,677
In a way, he did look like
he was enjoying the job.

806
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:24,638
It's true that these calcium
and vitamin supplements

807
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:26,598
are good for you.

808
00:45:26,682 --> 00:45:28,016
I'm speaking from experience.

809
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:30,144
I get that money is important,

810
00:45:30,727 --> 00:45:33,063
but why would that young guy
waste his time with a job like that?

811
00:45:33,397 --> 00:45:35,607
Was I really wrong about you?

812
00:45:36,066 --> 00:45:37,109
Lee Jun-ha.

813
00:45:40,696 --> 00:45:42,030
-Hello.
-Hello.

814
00:45:42,114 --> 00:45:43,240
Come on in.

815
00:45:43,323 --> 00:45:44,700
HYOJA EXHIBIT HALL

816
00:45:44,825 --> 00:45:46,243
Hello, you're back.

817
00:45:47,411 --> 00:45:48,287
-Hello.
-Hello.

818
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:49,538
-Go on in.
-Please go in.

819
00:45:51,623 --> 00:45:53,250
Are you returning this?
I'll take care of it.

820
00:45:53,333 --> 00:45:54,668
This isn't important.

821
00:45:54,751 --> 00:45:56,378
I have to talk to you about something.

822
00:45:56,462 --> 00:45:57,880
Can you spare me a moment?

823
00:45:57,963 --> 00:46:00,549
I'm a little busy right now,
so I'll talk to you later.

824
00:46:00,799 --> 00:46:02,092
See you in a bit.

825
00:46:02,801 --> 00:46:04,511
Please go in. Go on in.

826
00:46:09,349 --> 00:46:10,392
Ma'am!

827
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:14,396
Is that a thimble or what?

828
00:46:14,605 --> 00:46:15,939
Do you want to watch a movie with me?

829
00:46:16,023 --> 00:46:16,899
I'm busy today.

830
00:46:16,982 --> 00:46:18,734
-Then how about tomorrow?
-I'll be busy tomorrow.

831
00:46:18,817 --> 00:46:19,776
What about the weekend?

832
00:46:19,860 --> 00:46:21,403
I have a feeling that I'll get sick.

833
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:23,530
-Can I take you out for a meal?
-I'm on a diet.

834
00:46:23,614 --> 00:46:25,699
-Then how about some salad?
-I'm allergic to leafy greens.

835
00:46:25,782 --> 00:46:27,618
-What about beef?
-I'm a Hindu.

836
00:46:27,701 --> 00:46:29,244
-Since when?
-Since yesterday.

837
00:46:30,704 --> 00:46:32,289
She sure doesn't let her guard down.

838
00:46:32,915 --> 00:46:33,999
You passed my test.

839
00:46:55,854 --> 00:46:56,897
You can have this.

840
00:46:57,231 --> 00:46:58,232
No, thank you.

841
00:46:58,315 --> 00:47:00,609
I'll just get myself another one.
Have this.

842
00:47:00,692 --> 00:47:02,194
I told you I don't want it.

843
00:47:13,205 --> 00:47:15,958
Everyone who wants a refund
is waiting at the office now.

844
00:47:25,467 --> 00:47:26,677
What's the matter?

845
00:47:27,010 --> 00:47:29,429
Please send this to my son.

846
00:47:30,389 --> 00:47:32,474
You mean, your son in Los Angeles, right?

847
00:47:32,683 --> 00:47:34,726
The same address as last time?

848
00:47:34,893 --> 00:47:36,144
Please do it for me.

849
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:38,814
Did the red ginseng arrive safely?

850
00:47:39,106 --> 00:47:40,148
It did.

851
00:47:40,315 --> 00:47:41,942
I checked, so don't worry.

852
00:47:42,025 --> 00:47:43,819
I'll send this first thing tomorrow.

853
00:47:43,944 --> 00:47:45,529
Thanks for your help, every single time.

854
00:47:45,737 --> 00:47:48,198
It must cost quite a bit
to send parcels overseas.

855
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:50,158
We can definitely take care
of expenses like this.

856
00:47:52,119 --> 00:47:55,289
You're all here. Please give me a moment.

857
00:47:55,372 --> 00:47:58,041
Ma'am, you're here to return that, right?

858
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:00,544
There are six of you here.

859
00:48:00,627 --> 00:48:02,087
With you, there are seven in total.

860
00:48:02,170 --> 00:48:03,630
Mr. Park will take care of it.

861
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:04,923
Please have a seat.

862
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:06,300
Have a seat.

863
00:48:07,217 --> 00:48:09,261
-Just a moment, please.
-Be careful.

864
00:48:12,055 --> 00:48:14,099
Gosh, I'm so sorry.

865
00:48:17,477 --> 00:48:18,687
You drive me bonkers.

866
00:48:18,770 --> 00:48:20,522
What on earth are you doing?

867
00:48:20,606 --> 00:48:22,858
-I'm sorry.
-Do you know how expensive this is?

868
00:48:22,983 --> 00:48:24,818
Do you see this logo here or not?

869
00:48:25,444 --> 00:48:26,320
I do.

870
00:48:26,403 --> 00:48:27,529
What does it say?

871
00:48:28,488 --> 00:48:29,406
"NASA"?

872
00:48:29,489 --> 00:48:30,657
That's right, you fool.

873
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:33,118
The National Aeronautics
and Space Administration

874
00:48:33,201 --> 00:48:36,079
developed this supplement.

875
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:39,124
Do you know how astronauts travel in space

876
00:48:39,207 --> 00:48:41,084
for hundreds of days
or up to multiple years,

877
00:48:41,168 --> 00:48:43,712
while living on things
that don't even look edible?

878
00:48:44,671 --> 00:48:46,256
It's all because of this supplement.

879
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:47,341
Do you want to hear a story?

880
00:48:47,424 --> 00:48:49,676
-Yes.
-In Arizona,

881
00:48:49,926 --> 00:48:51,720
-there were twin brothers.
-Okay.

882
00:48:51,803 --> 00:48:54,890
-And the older one became an astronaut.
-Yes.

883
00:48:55,015 --> 00:48:57,351
Once, the older brother was
out in space for two years,

884
00:48:57,434 --> 00:48:58,435
only taking this.

885
00:48:58,518 --> 00:49:00,103
-When he got back to Earth,
-Yes.

886
00:49:00,187 --> 00:49:02,856
they weren't twins anymore.

887
00:49:03,649 --> 00:49:05,901
-They looked like father and son.
-Oh, my.

888
00:49:05,984 --> 00:49:07,569
Do you know what happened?

889
00:49:07,653 --> 00:49:10,864
The older brother, who took this,
didn't age a bit

890
00:49:11,114 --> 00:49:12,658
while the younger brother did.

891
00:49:13,450 --> 00:49:14,785
It's that effective.

892
00:49:15,035 --> 00:49:16,536
To get my hands on this,

893
00:49:17,079 --> 00:49:18,914
I had to ask so many people for help.

894
00:49:18,997 --> 00:49:21,124
I bought them millions of won
worth of drinks.

895
00:49:21,583 --> 00:49:23,085
-I see.
-My goodness.

896
00:49:23,168 --> 00:49:25,504
Why couldn't you get some more?

897
00:49:25,671 --> 00:49:28,924
You can't get more
just because you want to.

898
00:49:29,007 --> 00:49:31,551
It's not even for sale.

899
00:49:31,635 --> 00:49:33,512
I just got some for myself.

900
00:49:33,595 --> 00:49:34,638
Why isn't it for sale?

901
00:49:34,721 --> 00:49:37,015
Sadly, it has one drawback.

902
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:39,184
It weakens your bones.

903
00:49:39,601 --> 00:49:43,188
When astronauts come back
to Earth after some years,

904
00:49:43,271 --> 00:49:45,857
they can't walk properly because
their bones have become weak.

905
00:49:46,108 --> 00:49:48,568
So it's useless?

906
00:49:48,944 --> 00:49:50,779
You don't understand.

907
00:49:51,071 --> 00:49:54,574
We sell calcium supplements, right?

908
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:58,036
They're a perfect combination.

909
00:49:58,120 --> 00:50:01,707
This weakens your bones,
and the calcium strengthens them.

910
00:50:09,256 --> 00:50:11,675
Hey. "NASA".

911
00:50:12,217 --> 00:50:14,761
It's obviously fake.

912
00:50:15,053 --> 00:50:17,681
You've been doing this for years.
Why isn't your acting

913
00:50:17,764 --> 00:50:19,015
getting any better?

914
00:50:19,182 --> 00:50:21,601
We might get caught because of you.

915
00:50:21,685 --> 00:50:23,770
Acting is too difficult for me.

916
00:50:23,937 --> 00:50:25,939
I'm too nice by nature.

917
00:50:26,064 --> 00:50:29,609
Am I a good actor
because I'm mean by nature?

918
00:50:30,986 --> 00:50:34,406
If you think about it,
Jun-ha is incredible.

919
00:50:35,157 --> 00:50:36,867
He is so good. So good.

920
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:40,579
How can he fool people so perfectly?

921
00:50:40,746 --> 00:50:43,999
Hey. This job isn't really for him.

922
00:50:44,624 --> 00:50:47,919
But we're making money
thanks to him. So be nice to him.

923
00:50:48,295 --> 00:50:51,506
-I have to be nice to him?
-You complain too much.

924
00:50:58,638 --> 00:50:59,681
Hee-seon!

925
00:51:00,432 --> 00:51:01,767
Hee-seon!

926
00:51:03,101 --> 00:51:05,562
I saw her here.

927
00:51:06,146 --> 00:51:07,314
Hee-seon!

928
00:51:12,194 --> 00:51:13,904
HYOJA EXHIBIT HALL

929
00:51:15,363 --> 00:51:16,364
Please do me a favor.

930
00:51:16,448 --> 00:51:18,408
Did the red ginseng arrive safely?

931
00:51:18,492 --> 00:51:21,036
It did. I checked, so don't worry.

932
00:51:21,119 --> 00:51:22,829
I'll send this first thing tomorrow.

933
00:51:24,247 --> 00:51:25,624
This is crazy.

934
00:51:35,592 --> 00:51:37,969
Isn't that for the Chanel lady's son?

935
00:51:46,478 --> 00:51:49,648
The whole room is packed with boxes.

936
00:51:50,774 --> 00:51:52,025
How many are there?

937
00:51:52,776 --> 00:51:54,486
You must have done this many times.

938
00:51:54,861 --> 00:51:58,031
You never sent them after getting paid?

939
00:51:59,574 --> 00:52:02,702
This is different
from just selling supplements.

940
00:52:03,453 --> 00:52:05,580
How can you do this to the lady?

941
00:52:06,289 --> 00:52:08,708
How much do you get paid for this?
100 million won a year?

942
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:10,544
Is this the job you like?

943
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:15,423
I'm going to send them.
It's cheaper that way.

944
00:52:16,299 --> 00:52:17,801
You found your place.

945
00:52:17,884 --> 00:52:20,136
I knew you were a good talker,

946
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:22,889
but I didn't know
you were good at lying too.

947
00:52:23,515 --> 00:52:25,892
Move. I'll send them.

948
00:52:28,061 --> 00:52:30,897
-Ma'am.
-Stop me, and I'll report you.

949
00:52:31,648 --> 00:52:34,025
-You can't send them.
-You just don't want to.

950
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:36,570
I don't have her son's address.

951
00:52:38,488 --> 00:52:39,698
What?

952
00:52:40,657 --> 00:52:42,033
There is no son.

953
00:52:47,289 --> 00:52:48,748
Her son

954
00:52:50,375 --> 00:52:53,753
might be living abroad or dead.
Nobody knows.

955
00:52:54,754 --> 00:52:56,464
She never heard from him
after he left home.

956
00:52:56,548 --> 00:52:58,008
So I wanted to do something nice.

957
00:52:58,550 --> 00:53:02,846
She's become a lot happier
since she heard from her son again.

958
00:53:03,889 --> 00:53:06,224
Then why did you get paid?

959
00:53:08,310 --> 00:53:09,436
Nothing is for free.

960
00:53:09,519 --> 00:53:11,313
The lady is happy to hear from her son,

961
00:53:11,396 --> 00:53:12,647
and I'm happy to make some money.

962
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:14,441
It's a win-win situation.

963
00:53:15,358 --> 00:53:16,484
You...

964
00:53:17,319 --> 00:53:20,030
I'll tell her everything.

965
00:53:20,488 --> 00:53:22,032
-I'll...
-Go ahead.

966
00:53:23,408 --> 00:53:25,035
Go to the lady and tell her.

967
00:53:25,744 --> 00:53:28,121
"Your son has been out of reach for years.

968
00:53:28,538 --> 00:53:30,832
No one knows if he is still alive.

969
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:32,751
Maybe he is doing very well.

970
00:53:32,834 --> 00:53:35,754
He is just not talking to you."
Tell her that.

971
00:53:37,297 --> 00:53:38,423
Stop.

972
00:53:39,633 --> 00:53:40,842
Quit this job.

973
00:53:41,635 --> 00:53:44,763
This is my workplace.
Why do you tell me to quit my job?

974
00:53:44,888 --> 00:53:48,391
This is not just an ordinary
workplace. This is a bad place.

975
00:53:50,518 --> 00:53:52,228
What is an ordinary workplace?

976
00:53:53,688 --> 00:53:56,399
A company? A government office?

977
00:53:57,484 --> 00:53:58,652
It's all the same.

978
00:53:58,735 --> 00:54:00,403
They might look different,

979
00:54:00,487 --> 00:54:03,949
but they all work for their
own benefit, not anyone else's.

980
00:54:05,492 --> 00:54:07,702
I'll tell her everything.

981
00:54:09,037 --> 00:54:10,538
I'll make sure...

982
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:14,000
you quit working here.

983
00:54:14,542 --> 00:54:15,669
Fine, go ahead.

984
00:54:16,670 --> 00:54:18,672
Even if everyone asks for a refund
and stops coming here,

985
00:54:19,047 --> 00:54:20,632
what can I do?

986
00:54:22,926 --> 00:54:24,761
You stop coming here too.

987
00:54:27,013 --> 00:54:28,306
This is a bad place.

988
00:54:30,350 --> 00:54:31,726
Now you know.

989
00:54:33,520 --> 00:54:34,729
So don't ever come back here.

990
00:54:36,731 --> 00:54:39,401
All right. I won't.

991
00:54:39,776 --> 00:54:41,069
I can't stand

992
00:54:41,903 --> 00:54:44,781
this mean, unfair place anymore.

993
00:54:51,663 --> 00:54:52,789
Oh, my.

994
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:58,128
The thing is...

995
00:55:06,886 --> 00:55:09,764
HAPPY BEAUTY SALON

996
00:55:21,443 --> 00:55:23,111
I called a repairman. Leave it.

997
00:55:23,528 --> 00:55:24,863
Why would you waste money?

998
00:55:28,616 --> 00:55:30,410
It doesn't work. I already tried it.

999
00:55:39,377 --> 00:55:42,422
I said, it doesn't work!
Don't you hear me?

1000
00:56:14,079 --> 00:56:17,582
MIDNIGHT SNACK BAR

1001
00:56:34,682 --> 00:56:36,101
One udon, please.

1002
00:57:26,818 --> 00:57:28,111
Enjoy.

1003
00:57:42,208 --> 00:57:43,751
You ordered something else.

1004
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:47,130
You made some money?

1005
00:57:50,341 --> 00:57:53,678
From being loved by all the old people,

1006
00:57:54,512 --> 00:57:57,557
has your life improved now?

1007
00:58:07,025 --> 00:58:08,359
She says she misses you.

1008
00:58:12,447 --> 00:58:13,573
Hye-ja misses you.

1009
00:58:18,203 --> 00:58:21,122
Thanks to you, she had so much fun.

1010
00:58:22,790 --> 00:58:24,459
When she was with you,

1011
00:58:25,001 --> 00:58:26,461
even if all she had was

1012
00:58:26,794 --> 00:58:28,880
a bowl of udon and a bottle of soju
with you,

1013
00:58:30,048 --> 00:58:31,382
she felt happy.

1014
00:58:33,968 --> 00:58:37,096
Something urgent came up,
and she couldn't even call you.

1015
00:58:38,973 --> 00:58:41,518
She didn't want to leave either.

1016
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:45,063
I'm just trying to tell you
that you should love yourself more.

1017
00:58:45,146 --> 00:58:47,482
That will help you become
more generous with yourself.

1018
00:58:50,568 --> 00:58:52,070
That's heart-wrenching.

1019
00:58:54,906 --> 00:58:56,991
Don't let her suffer again.

1020
00:58:57,951 --> 00:59:01,746
I feel so bad for you.

1021
00:59:02,247 --> 00:59:04,415
Just in case you get the wrong idea,

1022
00:59:04,499 --> 00:59:06,960
I didn't nag her to tell me
like a stalker or something.

1023
00:59:07,043 --> 00:59:11,256
We were just having a casual
conversation and I found out.

1024
00:59:12,757 --> 00:59:14,384
You know Hye-ja, right?

1025
00:59:14,968 --> 00:59:17,512
My niece who is in Germany.

1026
00:59:18,638 --> 00:59:21,975
If she comes back from Germany, Hye-ja

1027
00:59:22,684 --> 00:59:24,894
will be very upset.

1028
00:59:27,605 --> 00:59:28,773
Kim Hye-ja.

1029
00:59:46,124 --> 00:59:48,459
Tell Hye-ja in Germany.

1030
00:59:48,793 --> 00:59:51,796
All I've done is bump into her
a few times in this neighborhood.

1031
00:59:52,380 --> 00:59:55,383
Tell her not to make such a big fuss
after only sharing a bowl of udon.

1032
00:59:55,800 --> 00:59:58,261
Whether she comes back to Korea
or whether she's upset or not,

1033
00:59:58,344 --> 00:59:59,846
tell her it's none of my business.

1034
01:00:01,639 --> 01:00:03,641
And let me ask you one last favor.

1035
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:09,522
Please stop your curiosity towards me
from now on.

1036
01:00:13,234 --> 01:00:14,986
I don't want to see you ever again.

1037
01:00:35,465 --> 01:00:37,342
Are you the Jun-ha I know?

1038
01:00:38,718 --> 01:00:41,638
That face is so unfamiliar and scary.

1039
01:00:45,350 --> 01:00:46,726
Eggs for sale.

1040
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:50,688
Check out these large, fresh eggs.

1041
01:00:51,814 --> 01:00:55,276
Yeong-su, come have some eggs.

